Danaher Corp. said that flat demand is likely to reduce forecasted 1989 earnings from continuing operations by $2.3 million to $3.5 million, or 10 cents to 15 cents a share.
Analysts had predicted 1989 earnings from continuing operations of about $47 million, or $2 a share, compared with earnings from continuing operations of $40 million, or $1.68 a share, in the previous year. 

The manufacturer of automotive products also said it sold its minority stake in Mohawk Rubber Co. for $45 million, which will result in an after-tax gain of $14 million, or 60 cents a share. 

